# Testing & Quality (Hackathon Mode)

## Pragmatic Testing Strategy

- Focus on critical path testing, not 100% coverage
- Test user-facing flows end-to-end over unit tests
- Use AI to generate tests after features are working

## Minimum Testing

- Smoke test: app loads without errors
- Auth flow: login/logout works (Supabase + frontend)
- CRUD: create and read transactions (and categories) via **FastAPI**
- Landing/dashboard: month totals and at least one chart render with data
- API: key FastAPI endpoints return expected responses (`/docs` try-it-out)

## Quick Validation Commands

```bash
cd frontend && npm run build
cd frontend && npm run lint
cd frontend && npx tsc --noEmit
cd backend && python -m compileall app 2>/dev/null || true
```

(Adjust Python paths if your package layout differs.)

## Error Monitoring

- React error boundary in `frontend/`
- Log with prefixes: `[AUTH]`, `[DB]`, `[API]` (frontend console / backend logger)
